definition: abbr. for Heilongjiang province 黑龍江|黑龙江[Hei1 long2 jiang1]
lit. dark sky and black earth (idiom)/fig. pitch dark/to black out/disorderly/troubled times

sentences.english: It was after dark and I was nervous, so when he pulled up I immediately jumped in the car.
sentences.chinese: 天黑了，我很紧张，看到车过来了就跳上去。

sentences.english: Whether day or night, summer or winter.
sentences.chinese: 不论白天黑夜，炎夏寒冬。

sentences.english: The torch arrived at the Guangzhou airport on Tuesday before dark.
sentences.chinese: 星期二天黑前，火炬抵达广州白云机场。

sentences.english: Stars were twinkling in the sky.
sentences.chinese: 天黑人静，星星在天上闪烁。

sentences.english: I got to get this truck unloaded and on the way back to the ware house before dark.
sentences.chinese: 我得把这车货卸完，在天黑前赶回仓库去呐。

sentences.english: Regardless of wind and rain, day and night, with cat travel.
sentences.chinese: 无论刮风下雨，白天黑夜，带着猫猫去旅行。
天黑前我们可以到达伦敦。

sentences.english: It was dark, and we could not make out who was coming along the road.
sentences.chinese: 天黑了，我们看不清是谁向我们走来。

sentences.english: "I'll have it back to you by this evening, " Dooku said, hurrying out.
sentences.chinese: “我天黑之前就还给你，”杜库说着就匆忙离开了。

sentences.english: If you thought that initially then it was impossible, but then the rain came.
sentences.chinese: 如果你想想那真是不可思议，但之后就天黑黑落雨鸟。

sentences.english: And by the time I get home, it's dark.
The love game is never called off on account of darkness.
sentences.chinese: 恋爱游戏并不会因为天黑就可以腰斩的。

sentences.english: The worry of her family, ZiShu advised him to action after dark.
sentences.chinese: 海天担心自己的家人，子书劝他天黑再行动。

sentences.english: Dark and slippery road, complex society.
For night and day belong to love.
sentences.chinese: 无论白天黑夜，爱长伴你左右。

sentences.english: You must get there by all means before dark.
sentences.chinese: 你们一定要在天黑以前到达那里。

definition: color of the sky/time of day, as indicated by the color of the sky/weather
in the evening/when night falls/towards evening/at night fall/at dusk
to grope about in the dark
midnight/in the middle of the night
time/period during the day/one of the 12 two-hour periods enumerated by the earthly branches 地支
to hold a lamp/to light a lamp
to hasten on with one's journey/to hurry on
